<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>{{ config.report_title | default(project ~ " Security Assessment") }}</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      color-scheme: dark;
      --bg: #0b0d10;
      --panel: #151920;
      --panel-2: #1d232c;
      --text: #eef2f6;
      --muted: #98a2b3;
      --line: #2b3440;
      --accent: #ef4444;
      --accent-2: #38bdf8;
      --ok: #22c55e;
      --warn: #f59e0b;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }
    header {
      padding: 40px 28px 28px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #171b22 0%, #0b0d10 100%);
    }
    main { max-width: 1180px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 28px; }
    h1 { margin: 0; font-size: 34px; letter-spacing: 0; }
    h2 { margin: 0 0 16px; font-size: 22px; }
    h3 { margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .subtitle { color: var(--muted); margin-top: 8px; }
    .brand { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 800; font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; }
    .grid { display: grid; gap: 16px; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(210px, 1fr)); margin: 24px 0; }
    .metric, section, details {
      background: var(--panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 18px;
    }
    .metric strong { display: block; font-size: 28px; }
    .metric span, .muted { color: var(--muted); }
    section { margin: 18px 0; }
    details { margin: 12px 0; }
    summary { cursor: pointer; font-weight: 700; }
    code, pre {
      font-family: "JetBrains Mono", "SFMono-Regular", Consolas, monospace;
      background: #0f1319;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 6px;
    }
    code { padding: 2px 5px; }
    pre { padding: 14px; overflow-x: auto; white-space: pre-wrap; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; }
    th, td { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); padding: 10px 8px; text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }
    th { color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .finding { border-left: 4px solid var(--accent); background: var(--panel-2); padding: 14px; border-radius: 6px; margin: 12px 0; }
    .severity { color: var(--warn); font-weight: 800; }
    .search { width: 100%; padding: 12px 14px; background: #0f1319; border: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--text); border-radius: 6px; margin: 12px 0 18px; }
    .gallery { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: 14px; }
    .shot img { width: 100%; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 6px; background: #050608; }
    .timeline { border-left: 2px solid var(--accent); padding-left: 18px; }
    .timeline-item { margin: 0 0 14px; }
    .time { color: var(--accent-2); font-weight: 800; }
    .bar { height: 9px; background: #0f1319; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 999px; overflow: hidden; }
    .bar span { display: block; height: 100%; background: var(--accent); }
    footer { color: var(--muted); padding: 30px 28px; text-align: center; }
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      h1 { font-size: 26px; }
      main, header { padding-left: 16px; padding-right: 16px; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <div class="brand">DRAGON Report Generator</div>
    <h1>{{ config.report_title | default(project ~ " Security Assessment") }}</h1>
    <div class="subtitle">Generated {{ generated_at }} for project <strong>{{ project }}</strong></div>
  </header>
  <main>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="metric"><strong>{{ stats.total_commands }}</strong><span>Commands tracked</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><strong>{{ stats.total_evidence }}</strong><span>Evidence artifacts</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><strong>{{ grouped_commands | length }}</strong><span>Activity categories</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><strong>{{ findings | length }}</strong><span>Auto summaries</span></div>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Executive Summary</h2>
      <p>{{ executive_summary }}</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Engagement Statistics</h2>
      {% set max_count = (stats.category_counts.values() | list | max) if stats.category_counts else 1 %}
      {% for category, count in stats.category_counts.items() %}
      <p><strong>{{ category }}</strong> <span class="muted">{{ count }}</span></p>
      <div class="bar"><span style="width: {{ (count / max_count * 100) | round }}%"></span></div>
      {% endfor %}
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Methodology</h2>
      <p>Testing activity was reconstructed from operator commands, imported evidence artifacts, and project notes. Commands were categorized into common penetration testing phases and redacted before report generation.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Activity Review</h2>
      <input class="search" id="search" placeholder="Search commands, categories, and evidence..." aria-label="Search report">
      {% for category, items in grouped_commands.items() %}
      <details open class="searchable">
        <summary>{{ category }} ({{ items | length }})</summary>
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Time</th><th>Activity</th><th>Command</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
          {% for command in items %}
            <tr><td>{{ command.timestamp }}</td><td>{{ command.activity }}</td><td><code>{{ command.command }}</code></td></tr>
          {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </details>
      {% endfor %}
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Findings</h2>
      {% for finding in findings %}
      <div class="finding searchable">
        <div class="severity">{{ finding.severity }}</div>
        <h3>{{ finding.title }}</h3>
        <p>{{ finding.summary }}</p>
        <p><strong>Recommendation:</strong> {{ finding.recommendation }}</p>
      </div>
      {% else %}
      <p class="muted">No findings were automatically summarized. Add validated issues to project notes or evidence before final delivery.</p>
      {% endfor %}
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Evidence</h2>
      <div class="gallery">
      {% for item in evidence if item.kind == "screenshot" %}
        <div class="shot searchable"><img src="{{ item.excerpt }}" alt="{{ item.title }}"><p>{{ item.title }}<br><span class="muted">{{ item.path }}</span></p></div>
      {% endfor %}
      </div>
      {% for item in evidence if item.kind == "output" %}
      <details class="searchable">
        <summary>{{ item.title }} - {{ item.path }}</summary>
        <pre>{{ item.excerpt }}</pre>
      </details>
      {% else %}
      <p class="muted">No text evidence files were imported.</p>
      {% endfor %}
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Timeline</h2>
      <div class="timeline">
      {% for event in timeline %}
        <div class="timeline-item searchable"><span class="time">{{ event.time }}</span> <strong>{{ event.title }}</strong><br><span class="muted">{{ event.category }} - {{ event.details }}</span></div>
      {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Recommendations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Validate all automated scanner findings manually.</li>
        <li>Prioritize remediation based on exploitability, exposure, and business impact.</li>
        <li>Retain evidence securely and distribute reports only through approved channels.</li>
        <li>Review authentication, monitoring, and patch management controls for tested assets.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Conclusion</h2>
      <p>The engagement activity captured by DRAGON provides a structured basis for a professional security assessment report. Final delivery should include analyst-validated findings, client scope confirmation, and remediation ownership.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <footer>Generated by DRAGON Report Generator</footer>
  <script>
    const search = document.getElementById('search');
    search?.addEventListener('input', () => {
      const term = search.value.toLowerCase();
      document.querySelectorAll('.searchable').forEach((node) => {
        node.style.display = node.textContent.toLowerCase().includes(term) ? '' : 'none';
      });
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
